attributes.title: save yourself and the lives of many others
attributes.review: this app has caused extreme distress in my life. as soon as i opened up the app to show a dirty, soggy, nasty looking cheeto, i was struck with the worst luck imaginable. first off, a cat in my house started cackling maniacally. almost human like. she walked along the walls and my ceilings and followed me into my bathroom while i took a massive 💩!! the worst part? the cat isn’t mine!! it crawled from the depths of my sewers. not to mention, it was a ginger cat, showing her alliance to our current saggy, wrinkly raisin leader. then, when the cat finally liquified and melted back into the sewer with pennywise (he’s real, i saw him and he asked me if i wanted my boat back), i turned on the tv to find sesame street was no longer streaming on any channel. i had to watch cats: the musical. and it was on a loop for hours. somehow, my remote had turned into a giant booger and i could not turn off the tv. the following day, i called an electrician to turn off the power to my entire house as that was the only way i could turn the tv off at that point. it ended up causing a global shutdown of all electricity for days. i don’t blame tony, i blame this god forsaken app. fortunately, since i couldn’t charge my phone anymore, my phone died and this app was no longer active. it’s curse had been temporarily broken. so, as soon as the power came back on, i immediately deleted the app. it wasn’t quick enough to avoid kranch from raining out of the sky, but it ended the suffering of millions. i will never be the same. this app should not exist at the cost of all of our lives. save yourself.
